### Issue description

`RichTextBox.GetCharIndexFromPosition()` unconditionally limits the result to `Text.Length - 1`.
So it never returns the position behind the last character.

```
            var wpt = new Point(pt.X, pt.Y);
            int index = (int)User32.SendMessageW(this, (User32.WM)User32.EM.CHARFROMPOS, IntPtr.Zero, ref wpt);

            string t = Text;
            // EM_CHARFROMPOS will return an invalid number if the last character in the RichEdit
            // is a newline.
            //
            if (index >= t.Length)
            {
                index = Math.Max(t.Length - 1, 0);
            }

            return index;
```

### Steps to reproduce

Set a (single-line) `Text` without a newline at the end.
Call `RichTextBox.GetCharIndexFromPosition()` with click location at / behind the last character.

